
To compile and run Picasso from the sources you will need sbt 0.12 (or a more recent version).
The instructions to download and install sbt are found at http://www.scala-sbt.org/

After compiling Picasso with sbt, Picasso can be run using the runGraph.sh or runBasic.sh scripts.

When proving termination of depth-bounded processes Picasso uses the additional tools:
    ARMC http://www7.in.tum.de/~rybal/armc/,
    Princess http://www.philipp.ruemmer.org/princess.shtml,
    Z3 http://z3.codeplex.com/

Further informations at: http://pub.ist.ac.at/~zufferey/picasso/
